38 //
39 // Defines the QuadrotorCoupled6D class, which uses PositionVelocity as the
40 // state and QuadrotorControl as the control, and models the system as a single
41 // coupled 6D system.
42 //
44

57 using state::PositionVelocity;
58 using control::QuadrotorControl;
59 
60 class QuadrotorCoupled6D :
61  public Dynamics<PositionVelocity, QuadrotorControl, Empty> {
62 public:
63  ~QuadrotorCoupled6D() {}
64  explicit QuadrotorCoupled6D()
65  : Dynamics() {}
66  explicit QuadrotorCoupled6D(const QuadrotorControl& u_lower,
67  const QuadrotorControl& u_upper)
68  : Dynamics(u_lower, u_upper) {}
69 
70  // Derived classes must be able to give the time derivative of state
71  // as a function of current state and control.
72  inline PositionVelocity Evaluate(
73  const PositionVelocity& x, const QuadrotorControl& u) const {
74  // Check initialization.
75  if (!initialized_)
76  throw std::runtime_error("QuadrotorCoupled6D: uninitialized call to Evaluate.");
77 
78  // Position derivatives are just velocity.
79  const Vector3d position_dot(x.Velocity());
80 
81  // Velocity derivatives are given by simple trigonometric functions
82  // of the pitch/roll, scaled by G since we assume that thrust is
83  // approximately equal to G.
84  const Vector3d velocity_dot(u.thrust * std::tan(u.pitch),
85  -u.thrust * std::tan(u.roll),
86  u.thrust - constants::G);
87 
88  return PositionVelocity(position_dot, velocity_dot);
89  }
90 
91  // Derived classes must be able to compute an optimal control given
92  // the gradient of the value function at the specified state.
93  // In this case (linear dynamics), the state is irrelevant given the
94  // gradient of the value function at that state.
95  inline QuadrotorControl OptimalControl(
96  const PositionVelocity& x, const PositionVelocity& value_gradient) const {
97  // Check initialization.
98  if (!initialized_)
99  throw std::runtime_error("QuadrotorCoupled6D: uninitialized call to OptimalControl.");
100 
101  // Set each dimension of optimal control to upper/lower bound depending
102  // on the sign of the gradient in that dimension. We want to minimize the
103  // inner product between the projected gradient and control.
104  // If the gradient is 0, then sets control to zero by default.
105  QuadrotorControl c;
106  c.yaw_rate = 0.0;
107  c.pitch = (value_gradient.Vx() < 0.0) ? u_upper_.pitch : u_lower_.pitch;
108  c.roll = (value_gradient.Vy() > 0.0) ? u_upper_.roll : u_lower_.roll;
109  c.thrust = (value_gradient.Vz() < 0.0) ? u_upper_.thrust : u_lower_.thrust;
110 
111  return c;
112  }
113 
114  // Convert to the appropriate service response type.
115  inline Empty ToRos() const {
116  throw std::runtime_error("QuadrotorCoupled6D: ToRos is unimplemented.");
117  return Empty();
118  }
119 
120  // Convert from the appropriate service response type.
121  inline void FromRos(const Empty& res) {
122  throw std::runtime_error("QuadrotorCoupled6D: FromRos is unimplemented.");
123  }
124 
125 }; //\class QuadrotorCoupled6D
